      "date": "2025-04-06 22:31:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nIt looks like all of the autoMakefiles are basically empty at this point.  It isn't clear if this patch is even worthwhile instead of the next patch that just deletes the files completely?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "86fd36ff09f396c09ea50d42ba53b9ccfb004d6d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2025-04-06 22:44:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nIt looks like the _DATA suffix is used by automake when generating autoMakefiles, like progname_CPPFLAGS and progname_SOURCES and progname_LDADD and progname_DEPENDENCIES is in Makefiles?\n\nIn any case, this patch and the next one are failing *every* build in Jenkins (not just a single random failure), so clearly this variable is needed, as is the autoMakefile.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fbe42b9cabf36d21ee25f244573007a571f4fc94",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2025-04-06 22:50:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> \n> It looks like the _DATA suffix is used by automake when generating autoMakefiles, like progname_CPPFLAGS and progname_SOURCES and progname_LDADD and progname_DEPENDENCIES is in Makefiles?\n> \n> In any case, this patch and the next one are failing *every* build in Jenkins (not just a single random failure), so clearly this variable is needed, as is the autoMakefile.\n\nYeah, these _DATA are totally needed (for now). We need an incantation in the top-level autoMakefile to add all .ko to the _DATA. I have an idea of how to make it work. Eventually, we won't need automake for the Lustre kernel build.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
